      <hr size="3" width="100%" class="c3" />
      <span class="c1"><u>In General</u></span>
    </div>
    <div class="c7">
      <p>
        Please e-mail <a href="<!--#include virtual="/cgi-bin/emailHref.php?email=tom@yoset.org" -->"><span
        class="c5">Tom Yoset</span></a> if you have comments, requests,
        specific questions, or suggestions for additions to this site.  Thank
        you.<br />
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="biography" name="biography"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="biography.shtml"><span class="c1">Biography</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><i><b>Last revised on 10 April 2000.</b></i></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        An index to biographical sketches appearing in the standard reference
        works on the county has been completed, and additional works are now
        being indexed.  The most recent additions are John W. Jordan&#39;s
        unreliable but nevertheless useful <a
        href="biography/1915.html">1915</a> compilation of lineages, and a 1903
        account of the Crawford County bench and bar.  The index contains links
        to some of the indexed sketches, including all of those from the <a
        href="biography/1876/people.html">1876</a> atlas.  <a
        href="contributors.shtml">Kathy Cook</a> is now copying sketches from
        the 1885 county history; other sketches will be added upon request.
      </p>
      <a id="cemetery" name="cemetery"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="cemetery.html"><span class="c1">Cemeteries</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><i><b>Last revised on 1 June 1999.</b></i></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        A rudimentary guide to cemetery locations, indexes, etc., has been
        started.  Additions and corrections would be welcomed.
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="census" name="census"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="census.html"><span class="c1">Census</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><b><i>Last revised on 29 April 2001.</i></b></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        The <a href="census/1860US-m.html">1860 U.S. Census mortality
        schedules</a> have been added, the <a href="census/1850US-m.html">1850
        U.S. Census mortality schedules</a> have been revised, and a combined
        <a href="census/mort.html">index</a> prepared.  The index to the <a
        href="census/1880US-m.html">1880 U.S. Census mortality schedules</a> is
        being revised.  Posting of the <a href="census/1840US.html">1840 U.S.
        Census</a>, being copied for this site by <a
        href="contributors.shtml">Diana L. Watson</a>, has begun with Summerhill
        Township.
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="court" name="court"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="court.html"><span class="c1">Courthouse</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><b><i>Last revised on 25 May 1999.</i></b></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Renamed from &quot;Court Records&quot; and undergoing revision.  The
        most recent additions are nineteenth century <a
        href="court/adopt.html">adoptions</a> and <a
        href="court/unprobated.html">unprobated wills</a>.
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="history" name="history"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="history.html"><span class="c1">History</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><b><i>Last revised on 24 March 2001.</i></b></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Alfred Huidekoper&#39;s account of the county published in <a
        href="history/1850.html">1850</a>, in answer to a questionnaire from
        the Historical Society of Pennsylvania, has been copied for this site
        by <a href="contributors.shtml">Robin Brown</a>.*<br />
        <br />
        With the addition of chapters covering Sadsbury, South Shenango,
        Sparta, Spring, Steuben, Summerhill, and Summit Townships, all township
        and borough sketches published in the <a
        href="history/1885/townships.html">1885</a> county history are now
        included at this site.<br />
        <br />
        <a href="contributors.shtml">Beverly Hopkins</a> of Erie, PA, has
        completed copying the township histories found in the <a
        href="history/1876/townships.html">1876</a> atlas for this site, and
        has begun to copy those printed in the <a
        href="history/1874/townships.html">1874</a> gazetteer (Athens is the
        latest township to be added).*  Every-name indexes to the copied
        sections of the 1874 gazetteer and the 1876 atlas have also been
        prepared (and appear nowhere else but at this site).<br />
        <br />
        <a href="contributors.shtml">Mary C. Fyda-Mar</a> of California has
        completed copying the township and borough sketches found in the <a
        href="history/1879/Part1.html">1879</a>-80 county directory, and an
        index to those sketches has been added.<br />
        <br />
        Guides to <a href="history/townships.html">Historical Township
        Boundaries</a> and <a href="history/boroughs.html">Historical Borough
        Boundaries</a> have been posted, showing the formation of these
        political subdivisions and their boundary changes.<br />
        <br />
        Notes on Methodist and Prebyterian Churches have been copied for a
        section on church history.
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="places" name="places"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="places.html"><span class="c1">Places</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><b><i>Last revised on 24 February 2000.</i></b></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        This section is being developed as a listing of geographical places,
        together with links to any pages dealing specifically with each place
        included.
      </p>
      <br />
      <a id="vital" name="vital"></a>
      <div class="c4">
        <a href="vital.html"><span class="c1">Vital Records</span></a><br />
        <span class="c6"><b><i>Last revised on 6 January 1999.</i></b></span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Additional information on obtaining vital records is being added, and
        the possibility of including the Meadville death records is being
        explored.
      </p>
